!! Core Concept
''The Selfish Gene'' (1976) by Richard Dawkins argues that the gene, not the individual or species, is the fundamental unit of selection. Organisms are merely "survival machines" built by genes to ensure their own replication.

!! Key Themes
* '''Gene-Centered View:''' Evolution acts on replicators (genes) rather than vehicles (bodies).
* '''Replicator Qualities:''' Longevity, fecundity, and copying-fidelity.
* '''The Meme:''' A unit of cultural evolution (ideas, tunes, catchphrases) that spreads through imitation.